IDB Holding, Israel Corp., Orckit, Xfone: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-05T06:36:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/idb-holding-israel-corp-orckit-xfone-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the
company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index fell 1.5 percent to 1,227.95 in  Tel Aviv .  Bank of Jerusalem (JBNK)  Ltd: The bank’s ilA+ rating
was placed on “creditwatch” at Standard & Poor’s Maalot. The
shares were little changed at 5.43 shekels.  IDB Holding Corp. (IDBH IT): The holding company said it
completed the acquisition of Maariv Holdings Ltd. (MARV IT) and
Chairman Nochi Dankner was named as a director of Maariv. IDB
declined 3.7 percent to 83.62 shekels.  Israel Corp. (ILCO IT): Sammy Ofer, whose family holdings
include Israel Corp.,  Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL)  ,  Oil
Refineries Ltd. (ORL)   and  Mizrahi Tefahot Bank Ltd. (MZTF)  , died at 89 on June 3 after a prolonged illness and will be
buried in Tel Aviv today. Israel Corp. dropped 2.5 percent to
3,550 shekels.  Orckit Communications Ltd. (ORCT)  : The maker of
telecommunications equipment said it expects to generate gross
proceeds of about 28.9 million shekels ($8.6 million) from bond
offerings. Orckit fell 3.6 percent to 8.018 shekels.  Xfone Inc. (XFN)  : The provider of long-distance voice
and data services said it extended its fiber network to
Littlefield,  Texas . Xfone retreated 1.5 percent to 4.011
shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
